description:
This is one of those places you either love or you hate.

I'm rating this place just on the sichuan menu.  I didn't bother with the standard cantonese scoop and dump menu.

As a lunch spot for sichuan...this place is the bomb.  

I got two of the classics;

- tendons & tripe in chili oil;
- cucumbers in garlic & chili;

The tendons & tripe were straight up legit.  A cold dish, in a fiery chili oil.  Lots of texture.  Well cooked, then well preserved.  

Cucumbers in chili & garlic -- they cheated on this one, slathering it in a chili & garlic sauce that is probably used in multiple other dishes.  My usual experience is something more like a a pickled cucumber in chili & garlic.  still, the flavor was something that was in the sichuan school.

This place will never win awards for decor, customer service.  But the large numbers of Mandarin speakers coming in to eat who were not local American Born Chinese, is the ultimate vote of confidence.
